This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with end-to-end speech translation, which involves both speech recognition and machine translation. Additionally, the paper discusses a data augmentation technique, which is a common topic in natural language processing research. 

It could also belong to cs.SD (Sound) as it deals with audio input features and speech recognition. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely sub-category as the paper discusses overfitting and improving model performance through data augmentation. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possibility as the paper deals with improving the performance of an AI system through data augmentation. 

Finally, cs.SD (Signal Processing) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with audio signal processing techniques.
